{"id": "EUVD-2022-55840", "enisaUuid": "65d3ec36-3dd5-38f7-bc39-d8e26ee9beed", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmmc: alcor: fix return value check of mmc_add_host()\n\nmmc_add_host() may return error, if we ignore its return value, the memory\nthat allocated in mmc_alloc_host() will be leaked and it will lead a kernel\ncrash because of deleting not added device in the remove path.\n\nSo fix this by checking the return value and calling mmc_free_host() in the\nerror path.", "datePublished": "2025-12-30T15:30:28", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-30T15:30:28", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/289c964fe182ce755044a6cd57698072e12ffa6f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4a6e5d0222804a3eaf2ea4cf893f412e7cf98cb2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/29c5b4da41f35108136d843c7432885c78cf8272", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/48dc06333d75f41c2ce9ba954bc3231324b45914", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/60fafcf2fb7ee9a4125dc9a86eeb9d490acf23e2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e93d1468f429475a753d6baa79b853b7ee5ef8c0", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50858"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50858"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0aeb7672-681a-3b88-ba63-4e9141698e4a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c5413ad815a675b5c98a002353d8e96b44b164e9 <29c5b4da41f35108136d843c7432885c78cf8272"}, {"id": "239c2d55-51bb-3353-997b-657481d857cf", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "2e9e3ecc-181e-33b8-952a-4ff3bfd97606", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.163"}, {"id": "40984863-d3b8-304b-ae70-64227116529a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "c5413ad815a675b5c98a002353d8e96b44b164e9 <289c964fe182ce755044a6cd57698072e12ffa6f"}, {"id": "423c312b-e996-3e20-8ea7-a6ed5ef5fac0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.0"}, {"id": "4d4a8ab3-8f64-357a-a1f6-c68dd53ddf08", "product": {"name": "L